Description: # pygrape
        
        Pygrape is a python library for updating terminal output in realtime
        
        
        
        ### Usage
        
        ```python
        pip3 instlal pygrape
        ```
        
        ### Example
        
        ```python
        from pygrape import pygrape
        
        def main():
            writer = pygrape(0.05)
            print("Downloading pygrape.whl (2 MB)")
            bar = "█"
            for i in range(101):
                time.sleep(0.05)
                if i % 2 == 0:
                    bar += "█"
                writer.writer(" " + str(i) + "% |" + bar + "|")
                writer.flush()
            writer.stop()
        ```
        
